    "content": ""
  },
  {
    "line": 37,
    "content": "Scenario D reveals a strong linear relationship between path length and computational cost. As target distance increased from 10 to 60 grid units, search time increased from 0.079 ms to 0.223 ms, and expanded nodes increased from 18.7 to 55.9. This linear scaling is highly desirable from a computational perspective."
