    "line": 40,
    "content": ""
  },
  {
    "line": 41,
    "content": "This linear scaling property has important practical implications. It means that the computational cost of finding longer paths is predictable and manageable. For applications requiring pathfinding in large environments, this property ensures that the algorithm remains efficient even when searching for distant goals."
