  {
    "line": 46,
    "content": ""
  },
  {
    "line": 47,
    "content": "Comparing the four scenarios reveals a clear performance hierarchy. Scenario A (200×200 map) shows the highest computational cost with 1.641 ms search time and 479.7 expanded nodes, reflecting the inherent difficulty of large-scale pathfinding. Scenarios B, C, and D, all conducted on 50×50 maps, show much lower costs (0.151-0.155 ms search time, 38.9-43.1 expanded nodes), demonstrating that map size is the dominant factor affecting performance."
