  {
    "line": 53,
    "content": "The consistent superiority of Manhattan distance across all scenarios confirms its status as the optimal heuristic for grid-based pathfinding with eight-directional movement. The 6-fold reduction in expanded nodes compared to diagonal distance represents a significant efficiency gain that would be amplified in larger-scale applications."
